<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 (also known as Punta Gnifetti) (4,554 m) is a peak of the Monte Rosa massif in the Pennine Alps in Italy and Switzerland. 
<REF ID="836.2" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">The mountain</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
